    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Scheduler.CrystalReportTemplate",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table is a base table within a Microsoft SQL Server database, designed to store information about Crystal Report templates used in a scheduling application. Each record in this table represents a unique Crystal Report template, identified by a "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "TemplateID",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ". The table includes a path to the Crystal Report file, stored in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "CrystalReportPath",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " column. The table is linked to another table, "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Scheduler.ReportTemplate",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ", through a foreign key relationship on "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "TemplateID",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The table structure is relatively simple, consisting of only two columns. The relationships and indexing are straightforward, with a single primary key and foreign key constraint. The complexity is low due to the minimal number of columns and straightforward relationships."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Data Model Analysis"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
